    Glass grinding; and
    Polishing wastes;

      (d)
      Any pollutant, including, but not limited to oxygen demanding pollutants,eleased in the discharge at a flow rate, or concentration, or a combination ofoth, which causes interference with or compromises the structural integrity of

    the District&#8217;s wastewater system;

      (e)
      Any wastewater with heat in such amounts as will inhibit the biologicalctivity of processes in the District&#8217;s wastewater system resulting innterference. In no case shall wastewater be discharged by a User inemperatures in excess of one
        hundred forty degrees Fahrenheit (140° F) orixty degrees Centigrade (60° C), nor shall wastewater be discharged whichauses individually or in combination with other wastewater, the influent at theistrict&#8217;s wastewater treatment plant
        to have a temperature exceeding oneundred four degrees Fahrenheit (104° F) or forty degrees Centigrade (40° C),xcept where a variance from the one hundred forty degrees Fahrenheit (140° F)r sixty degrees Centigrade (60° C) discharge limit is authorized
        in writing byASA;


      (f)
      Any wastewater containing petroleum oil, non-biodegradable cutting oil, orroducts of mineral oil origin in amounts that will cause pass through ornterference;


      (g)
      Any wastewater containing pollutants which result in the presence of toxic,oxious or malodorous liquids, solids, gases, vapors, or fumes within theistrict’s wastewater system which alone or in interaction with other wastes,re capable of creating
        a public nuisance or hazard to humans or animals, areufficient to cause acute worker health and safety problems, or are sufficiento cause interference or pass through;


      (h)
      Any wastewater of objectionable color or tint not removed in the treatmentrocess, including, but not limited to, dye wastes and vegetable tanning wastes;

    Any trucked or hauled pollutants, except at discharge points that WASAesignates;

      (j)
      Wastewater containing any radioactive wastes or isotopes of such half-lifer concentration as may exceed limits that WASA establishes or applicable Stater National standards, cause pass through or interference or otherwise adverselympact the District’s
        wastewater system or cause or contribute to pollution;


